<font color="#FF0000">OFF TO SEE REAL MEN</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov  6 13:36:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all of you, esp. Tom and Cook.  Why do I keep coming back here was asked? Good question.  Obviously so Cook can have something to do (reading the archives) and the rest of you can focus your hatred.  Sadly that is the state of this site now.<br><br>
Tom, remember back to last Memorial Day?  This site got me to rethink many of my thoughts, and I ended up in Little Saigon at the Visiting Wall. Something I thought I would never do, ever in my life.  I realized I did not hate the Vietnamese, only one who was my neighbor.  The site provoked deep thoughts for me and others.  Fortunately, the others and I stay in touch b/c, but look what changed since then.<br><br>
From learning we have name calling, from thinking we have blind obedience, from challenging ideas we have crap. And it is all due to the take over of a gang of several, and we all know who they are.  I stretched the truth onece &quot;for effect&quot; as you guys often say, and I constantly hear about it. I have pointed out at least 25 outright lies and distortions by Cook, yet not a word from any of you, or him.  Cook only has one speed, blind hatred in first gear. He has never answered any of my challenges, he just attacks and calls names.  That is his right, to act like a bully, but where is the shame of the rest of you?<br><br>
Yea, I stick around to stir the pot, but that too is getting old. It takes two to have a conversation, and lately that just ain't happening here any more.  Tom, you of all have led the &quot;old gang&quot; down, and lost you once impartial thinking.  For you to lower yourself into name calling too is a real fall, and sad to see.<br><br>
Well DocDel, a better man than any of you in the pack will ever be, took the right path, and I think I will join him on it for some conversation.  <br><br>
John, your comments about who is and isn't a doctor was interesting, and new to me. I go by the academic model, not the battlefield one, but I agree, if ever a doctor truly existed, it was DocDel.<br><br>
If and when you boys can grow up and stop throwing insults, and get back to truth and dialogue, and stop being led by the nose by Cook (Yes Tom, you have evidence he was in nam, so what?).  If he wants to spend endless hours speculating about me, I hope he enjoys it.  Cook I will leave you with some clues. Long Beach State never had a Ph.D program. I got mine in Arizona, by the way.  Yes, I was in Israel in the summer of 1967, and if I knew how to attach a scanned photo, of me with Moishe Dayan I would, but I have it proudly on my wall. For those of you who don't know, he with the Minister of Defense and one of the key figures in the 1967 Six Day War.  I became a C.O. after seeing a war &quot;upclose and personal&quot;, but I was not &quot;in&quot; it. Never said I was. Never said my experience compared with battles in the Jungle either.<br><br>
Well boys, have at it.  Why am I here was asked? The answer is simple, because it was fun.
